<P ALIGN="CENTER"><FONT SIZE="-1" COLOR="GREEN"><I>Rig Veda</I>, tr. by Ralph T.H. Griffith, [1896], at sacred-texts.com</FONT></P><HR></p>  <h3 align="center" align="center">HYMN LXXI. Mitra-Varu&#7751;a.</h3>  
<p>1. O Varu&#7751;a and Mitra, ye who slay the foemen, come with might<br> To this our goodly sacrifice.<br> 2 For, Varu&#7751;a and Mitra, ye Sages are Rulers over all. Fill full our songs, for this ye can.<br> 3 Come to the juice that we have pressed. Varu&#7751;a, Mitra, come to drink<br> This Soma of the worshipper.</p>  
